MTN Nigeria Aims to Spend $1 Billion on Network Expansion, ThisDay Reports

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-03-11T08:35:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/mtn-nigeria-plans-1-billion-network-expansion-thisday-says.html
MTN  Nigeria , the country’s largest
mobile-phone operator, plans to spend $1 billion on expanding
its network this year,  ThisDay  reported, citing corporate
executive Wale Goodluck.  The unit of  South Africa ’s  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN)  will spend the
money on increasing its fiber optic capacity, acquiring base
stations and improving service quality, according to the Lagos-
based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at   dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 